  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Apetit Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Apetit (or the Company) is a leading meat trader and processor in Kosovo providing industrials and consumers with frozen meat, fresh meat cuts, and, cured meat products such as sujuk and prosciutto.   Apetit seeks to grow and modernize its operations.   To do so, the Company is planning to (i) establish a large and modern slaughterhouse, which will comply with EU regulations on food safety, (ii) integrate upstream by setting up a cattle farm, which will partly replace Apetits imports, and, (iii) powering all its facilities (the slaughterhouse, the farm and the meat processing plant) with solar panels.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The most significant, expected Project-level outcome is the provision of safe meat and associated products to the domestic consumers and expanded income opportunities for the local farmers. In addition, the Project will contribute to strengthening the competitiveness of Kosovo&apos;s meat processing sector by showcasing modern production practices and international food safety standards, which would be disseminated though demonstration and replication effects.</narrative>
  </description>
